 we didn’t really know, and later learn through the glimpses that Chris Perez graciously lets us peek in on, is how it all began. <br />To Selena, With Love, embraces a voice so authentic, so genuine, and so honest that readers can’t help but cry, smile, lament, grieve, and celebrate alongside with Chris on this incredibly touching journey.<br />Throughout the years, I’ve often thought about Chris Perez and the aftermath of what he must have emotionally and physically endured after Selena’s death. When I caught wind of his upcoming book, my curiosity was peaked. I must admit that while the book is cloaked in Selena, it is really as much about Chris as well. It is my hope that readers embrace his willingness to allow free access into an area of his life that he could have left private forever.<br />Told from the vantage point of one who “quietly observes from the fringes”, Chris lets the reader know point blank what both he and Selena agonizingly endured by living out their forbidden romance. The pictures he paints of Abraham’s despise reveal many hurtful moments that most persons would not have tolerated. But Chris prevailed, and does so still today in the face of truth as told from his perspective.<br />A point that Chris articulates well is that he fell in love with the “real” Selena. And that is the Selena he presents page by page, word by word. The examples he shares are intimate and simplistic, yet bring an extraordinarily powerful presence to Selena’s memory. This is not an easy task and Chris must be commended for letting his authentic spirit vividly recall the eternal love of his life.<br />I connected with many of the childhood memories Chris shared partly because we are from the same city and age range, but mostly because our economic backgrounds were similar. I found myself laughing when he mentioned his mom loving 55KTSA because my mom did as well. So much so, that I have pictures of me as a child covered in 55KTSA buttons and clothing she made for a radio sponsored contest!<br />I felt deep sadness in moments when Chris discusses being deemed unworthy of Selena’s affections. To me, this must have worn heavily on his core sense of self. Chris, however, ultimately transcends those feelings and comes to a place of assured certainty in both his love for Selena and of her love for him!<br />So many moments are retold with such precision that brief flashes of the Selena movie played in my brain. I especially enjoyed seeing Selena’s playful nature highlighted as one of her best attributes.<br />Chris will make you cry when retelling the painful moments of Selena’s death and his reactions that followed. The tear-jerker moment for me (and there were many) is his attempt at preserving her scent after her death. I won’t reveal the details but warn you that you better have a box of tissue nearby.<br />Ultimately, this book is about the resurrection of Chris Perez and his “struggle to find meaning in life again”. It is about freeing himself from the walls of his grief and deciding to return to the land of the living. This book is his “best I can” moment.<br />“I love you, Christopher,” Selena said. She always used my full name whenever things were serious or intense between us. ��Let’s never let anything between us change. Promise?” Her voice was as solemn as I’d ever heard it. “I promise,” I said, and told her how much I loved her, too. “I don’t know what I’d do if I ever lost you,” I confessed. <br />Chris Perez wrote a book, for Selena, and that’s how the story really ends.<br /></span></div></div></div></section></section><section class="ReviewCard__tags"><ul class="CollapsableList"></ul></section><footer class="SocialFooter"><div data-testid="stats" class="SocialFooter__statsContainer"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small Button--subdued"><span class="Button__labelItem">17 likes</span></button></div><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Butto