"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" role="presentation"><g stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><path class="RatingStar__fill" d="M12.4770229,1.34326985 L15.0891563,9.1315756 L23.4968842,9.1315756 C23.7747474,9.1315756 24,9.35682823 24,9.63469143 C24,9.79809886 23.9206399,9.95132779 23.7871766,10.0456121 L16.9959586,14.8432273 L19.5982827,22.6117477 C19.6865419,22.8752212 19.5445026,23.1603569 19.2810291,23.2486161 C19.1293386,23.2994298 18.9625235,23.2750752 18.8316924,23.1830139 L12.0000207,18.3758025 L5.1685337,23.1876292 C4.94136559,23.3476374 4.62749722,23.2931935 4.46748907,23.0660254 C4.37533831,22.9351963 4.35092131,22.7683321 4.4017231,22.616585 L7.00408269,14.8432273 L0.212864685,10.0456121 C-0.0140805533,9.88528803 -0.0680876559,9.57134421 0.0922364448,9.34439897 C0.186520784,9.21093568 0.339749724,9.1315756 0.503157148,9.1315756 L8.910885,9.1315756 L11.5230185,1.34326985 C11.6113744,1.0798288 11.8965622,0.937894292 12.1600033,1.02625024 C12.3095218,1.07639751 12.4268756,1.19375135 12.4770229,1.34326985 Z"></path></g></svg></span><span class="RatingStar RatingStar--small"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" role="presentation"><g stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><path class="RatingStar__backgroundFill" d="M12.4770229,1.34326985 L15.0891563,9.1315756 L23.4968842,9.1315756 C23.7747474,9.1315756 24,9.35682823 24,9.63469143 C24,9.79809886 23.9206399,9.95132779 23.7871766,10.0456121 L16.9959586,14.8432273 L19.5982827,22.6117477 C19.6865419,22.8752212 19.5445026,23.1603569 19.2810291,23.2486161 C19.1293386,23.2994298 18.9625235,23.2750752 18.8316924,23.1830139 L12.0000207,18.3758025 L5.1685337,23.1876292 C4.94136559,23.3476374 4.62749722,23.2931935 4.46748907,23.0660254 C4.37533831,22.9351963 4.35092131,22.7683321 4.4017231,22.616585 L7.00408269,14.8432273 L0.212864685,10.0456121 C-0.0140805533,9.88528803 -0.0680876559,9.57134421 0.0922364448,9.34439897 C0.186520784,9.21093568 0.339749724,9.1315756 0.503157148,9.1315756 L8.910885,9.1315756 L11.5230185,1.34326985 C11.6113744,1.0798288 11.8965622,0.937894292 12.1600033,1.02625024 C12.3095218,1.07639751 12.4268756,1.19375135 12.4770229,1.34326985 Z"></path></g></svg></span><span class="RatingStar RatingStar--small"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" role="presentation"><g stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><path class="RatingStar__backgroundFill" d="M12.4770229,1.34326985 L15.0891563,9.1315756 L23.4968842,9.1315756 C23.7747474,9.1315756 24,9.35682823 24,9.63469143 C24,9.79809886 23.9206399,9.95132779 23.7871766,10.0456121 L16.9959586,14.8432273 L19.5982827,22.6117477 C19.6865419,22.8752212 19.5445026,23.1603569 19.2810291,23.2486161 C19.1293386,23.2994298 18.9625235,23.2750752 18.8316924,23.1830139 L12.0000207,18.3758025 L5.1685337,23.1876292 C4.94136559,23.3476374 4.62749722,23.2931935 4.46748907,23.0660254 C4.37533831,22.9351963 4.35092131,22.7683321 4.4017231,22.616585 L7.00408269,14.8432273 L0.212864685,10.0456121 C-0.0140805533,9.88528803 -0.0680876559,9.57134421 0.0922364448,9.34439897 C0.186520784,9.21093568 0.339749724,9.1315756 0.503157148,9.1315756 L8.910885,9.1315756 L11.5230185,1.34326985 C11.6113744,1.0798288 11.8965622,0.937894292 12.1600033,1.02625024 C12.3095218,1.07639751 12.4268756,1.19375135 12.4770229,1.34326985 Z"></path></g></svg></span></span></div><span class="Text Text__body3"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/655159701">June 30, 2013</a></span></section><section class="ReviewText"><section class="ReviewText__content"><div class="TruncatedText"><div class="TruncatedText__text TruncatedText__text--5" data-testid="contentContainer"><div><span class="Formatted">	I read this book because I’ve been a Selena fan for almost 20 years and wanted to learn more about the person behind the image. Before I detail my thoughts on this book, let me first describe what Selena means to me.<br />	Selena entered my life on the day that she died. Because I was home sick that day, I caught a glimpse of the tragic news on the television programs I normally did not watch. Then, in the days that followed, I saw tributes to Selena which were ubiquuous in Texas, where I lived at the time. People expressed their sorrow with signage and banners on their cars, homes, trees and poles. Mainstream radio stations played her music and her voice captured me. A few months later, I read an article about how Chris Perez was coping with his loss. That’s when I became totally enmeshed with her. She was the same age as me and like me, had brown skin and black hair. Yet, she didn’t let racism thwart her ambition. She had accomplished so much, influenced so many, and had a plethora of plans for the future. I, on the other hand, was in a dark place in my own life. At the time, I hated my job, was confused about my goals, avoided my community, and worst of all, attracted a dreary set of peers. <br />	But I believe in death, from the other world, Selena resurrected me. Through listening to all her songs and reading about her, I purged all the negative energy from my spirit. I rewrote my job description, surrounded myself with energetic and positive people and not only got involved with the community, but climbed my way into a leadership position. It’s 18 years later, and my find myself in another valley, but after reading this book, I realized that Selena never turned 40, never had children and never got to actualize her dreams in life. But I still can. <br />	Now, about this book. I gave it an average rating because while it filled in a lot of gaps about Selena’s life, it didn’t grip me as I hoped it would. Maybe I’ve grown older and wiser and find it difficult to relate to Selena’s non-stop energy, impulsive behavior, and what I perceive as self-centeredness. For example, when Chris said he contemplated leaving Los Dinos to pursue his own interest in rock music, she threatened to leave him. While Chris wrote that he got over this, I thought it was manipulative, domineering and selfish on her part. Maybe he agreed to it at the time and today justifies it due to her tragic death, but had she still been alive, how long would anyone be able to put up with something like this? Second, when he discussed her buying dog after dog after dog, I thought it was immature and indulgent. If she wanted something, she got it; if she wanted to do something (like ride motorcycle), she did it—without thinking it through. Perhaps that works for a 20-something music star, but at some point, life teaches you that you can’t splurge on whatever you want, whenever you want and that not everything you do has a positive outcome. Unfortunately, Selena was robbed from living and could not gain this wisdom. <br />	Having said this, I think there was more to Selena than what Chris has shared in this book. I think she did have extensive wisdom, maturity and depth than what was described in these pages. I understand that Chris is a private person and is not obligated to share his deepest thoughts and feelings about Selena. Still, his antedotes and stories only touched the surface. I just shared how Selena changed me. I wish Chris had provided a more in-depth account of how Selena changed him. Sure, he does state that she changed him into a more loving person. But what I would have wanted to know more in-depth is:<br />•	How he was before he met Selena. For example, he mentions having girlfriends, but not experiencing anything deep. Well, what was that like? Why was he that way? How did his parents’ divorce and upbringing influence him?<br />•	What was it about Selena that changed him? Her forgiveness and understanding isn’t sufficient. Because of his parents’ divorce and humble beginnings, he had to have had trust issues. How did Selena change that. <br />•	How he dealt with the tragedy in terms of his emotions and actions. He mentions heavy drinking, drugs, depression and going crazy. But what were his days like? How was Selena’s family, who lived right next door, toward him? Did he contemplate killing himself? Did he go back to his old ways? Did he lose his zest for life?<br />•	How then did he come out of these dark days? How did Selena (in death) influence him? Again, he does mention the band he started, getting remarried and having kids. But I would have liked to hear more. How does his life with Selena influence him in the way he raises his children? Does he mention Selena to them? What about the mother of his children? I think her name is Vanessa and they’re now divorced. Did his life with Selena shadow and eventually end their marriage? Finally, how does he think Selena would have been today, had she not been killed?<br /><br />I am glad I read the book and by no means has it made me think less of Chris or Selena. I’m just saying I would like to have had more. It would have only strengthen Selena’s legacy.<br /><br /></span></div></div></div></section></section><section class="ReviewCard__tags"><ul class="CollapsableList"></ul></section><footer class="SocialFooter"><div data-testid="stats" class="SocialFooter__statsContainer"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small Button--subdued"><span class="Button__labelItem">12 likes</span></button></div><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small Button--subdued"><span class="Button__labelItem">2 comments</span></button></div></div><div data-testid="actions"><div class="SocialFooter__action"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem"><i class="Icon LikeIcon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M14.4813282,6.41129383 L14.586127,6.97676447 C14.5964421,7.03541935 14.6071117,7.09675198 14.6181364,7.1607667 L14.8551301,8.60363442 L17.440983,8.60363442 C18.1623576,8.60363442 18.8218187,9.01120377 19.1444272,9.65642083 L19.1708204,9.70920723 C19.4523479,10.2722622 19.4523479,10.9350066 19.1708204,11.4980616 L19.1180