ικές χώρες βρήκαν την δική τους Madonna (όντως την είχαν χαρακτηρίσει έτσι) , μπορούσαν πλέον οι νεαρές κοπέλες να ταυτιστούν με κάποια που τους έμοιαζε. Έγινε αστέρι γρήγορα αλλά με σκληρή δουλεία. Πάνω στην σκηνή γνώρισε και τον άντρα της, ήταν ο κιθαρίστας της, τον Chris Perez. Μετά από μόλις 8 μήνες σχέσης,παντρεύτηκαν. Η Selena ήταν μόλις 22 χρόνων.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eΤο 1995 η Selena δολοφονήθηκε. Όχι από κάποιον άγνωστο αλλά από μια γυναίκα που εμπιστευόταν και θεωρούσε όχι μόνο φίλη της αλλά και μητέρα. Και γιατί; Προδοσία, κατάχρηση της εμπιστοσύνης και κλέψιμο. Μια ζωή γεμάτη όνειρα έσβησε έτσι στα ξαφνικά. Χιλιάδες κόσμος επηρεάστηκε, και ακόμα και τώρα την θυμούνται με αγάπη.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eΟ Chris Perez δεν το ξεπέρασε ποτέ, ήταν και αυτός νεότατος μόνο 26 χρόνων όταν έχασε την γυναίκα του. Ακόμα και ο μετέπειτα γάμος του μετά από μια δεκαετία άντεξε μονάχα λίγα χρόνια. Αυτό το βιβλίο το έγραψε για να δείξει στον κόσμο την Selena έτσι όπως εκείνος την έβλεπε, με τα μάτια γεμάτα θαυμασμό.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eΤο βιβλίο είναι γραμμένο με αγά��η. Είναι δύσκολο να ξεπεράσεις έναν έρωτα όταν μπαίνει στην μέση ο θάνατος, ειδικά όταν είσαι νέος και ο έρωτας ζει ακόμα μέσα σου.. Μέσα από τις σελίδες του μας εξιστορεί το πως ερωτεύτηκε την Selena, ξαφνικά μέσα σε ένα αεροπλάνο γυρνώντας από το Ακαπούλκο. Την πρώτη φορά που είπαν σε αγαπώ σε μια πιτσαρία, κρυμμένοι από τον πατέρα της. Τις δυσκολίες που αντιμετώπισαν μιας και ο πατέρας της τραγουδίστριας ήταν αυστηρός και καταπιεστικός και δεν τους ήθελε μαζί, το πως κλέφτηκαν για να επισημοποιήσουν την σχέση τους και να γλυτώσουν από την καταπίεση. Αν και έμειναν δεμένοι με την οικογένεια της Selena μέχρι το τέλος της και ο Chris στηρίχτηκε πολύ σε εκείνους μετέπειτα.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eΟ Chris περιγράφει την Σελένα σαν μια σκληρά εργαζόμενη καλλιτέχνιδα, που αγαπούσε πολύ τους ανθρώπους. Ήταν γεμάτη ζωή, δεν φοβόταν τίποτα και ότι ήθελε το έκανε χωρίς να κάνει βήμα πίσω. Παρόλα αυτά κατά την διάρκεια της ανάγνωσης ένιωθα πως μερικές φόρες ήταν λίγο ανώριμη, μετά σκεφτόμουν βέβαια ότι ήταν τόσο νέα..\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eΜπορεί να καταλάβει κανείς πως ο Chris την λάτρευε, ότι ήθελε της το έδινε αλλά και εκείνη έμοιαζε να κρέμεται από εκείνον, γενικά ήταν ένα υπέροχο ζευγάρι. Προς το τέλος που μιλάει για το πως έμαθε για τον θάνατο της και πως αυτός τον επηρέασε ένιωσα μερικά δάκρυα να ετοιμάζονται να πέσουν στα μάγουλα μου. Την ταινία με την ζωή της Selenas δεν την είχε δει μέχρι πρόσφατα και φυσικά δεν είδε την σκηνή με την δολοφονία της, είναι πραγματικά σπαραχτικό.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eΜε λίγα λόγια μου άρεσε πάρα πολύ, νόμιζα πως θα βαρεθώ αλλά ούτε μια στιγμή δεν ένιωσα έτσι. Μάλιστα σε αρκετά σημεία είχα αγωνία να δω τι θα γίνει παρακάτω αν και ήδη γνώριζα. Αν κάποιος ενδιαφέρεται το προτείνω!","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/9830594?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2058983731"},"likeCount":25,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":2,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:2396315":{"id":2396315,"__typename":"User","legacyId":2396315,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1309593013i/2396315._UY200_CR33,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":9,"viewableName":"Kayla","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/2396315-kayla","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":30},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.fjvcUaa6xbBfE2lWGxBnlQ":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.fjvcUaa6xbBfE2lWGxBnlQ","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.OBfo01am2p3jpPbtKc27LQ"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:2396315"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1633102702454,"createdAt":1334826959000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1334827492000,"text":"On April 17, 2012, I got to meet Chris Perez at his book signing. It was a wonderful experience. In a weird way, I could feel that Selena's presence was with him. I know she is looking down upon him, smiling ever so proudly. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eTo Selena, With Love is an emotional roller coaster of a book. What I mean by that is you will experience all the emotions that Chris is feeling in the book. From his joy when Selena started talking to him on the plane to pure bliss when they first said \"I love you.\" Then of course, you will feel his pain from when he received the shocking news about his beloved wife up to sadness felt at her funeral. If a book has yet to make you cry, I guarantee you this will be the book to make tears turn into waterfalls. This book is a definite recommendation to everyone.","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/2396315?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/315097729"},"likeCount":22,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":1,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:9347538":{"id":9347538,"__typename":"User","legacyId":9347538,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1336425459i/9347538.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":1,"viewableName":"Venus","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/9347538-venus","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":0},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.RR14brCbheHhoQ7XCuTlEw":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.RR14brCbheHhoQ7XCuTlEw","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.OBfo01am2p3jpPbtKc27LQ"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:9347538"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1637036656161,"createdAt":1336425489000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1336425658000,"text":"We all know how the story ends. What we didn’t really know, and later learn through the glimpses that Chris Perez graciously lets us peek in on, is how it all began. \u003cbr /\u003eTo Selena, With Love, embraces a voice so authentic, so genuine, and so honest that readers can’t help but cry, smile, lament, grieve, and celebrate alongside with Chris on this incredibly touching journey.\u003cbr /\u003eThroughout the years, I’ve often thought about Chris Perez and the aftermath of what he must have emotionally and physically endured after Selena’s death. When I caught wind of his upcoming book, my curiosity was peaked. I must admit that while the book is cloaked in Selena, it is really as much about Chris as well. It is my hope that readers embrace his willingness to allow free access into an area of his life that he could have left private forever.\u003cbr /\u003eTold from the vantage point of one who “quietly observes from the fringes”, Chris lets the reader know point blank what both he and Selena agonizingly endured by living out their forbidden romance. The pictures he paints of Abraham’s despise reveal many hurtful moments that most persons would not have tolerated. But Chris prevailed, and does so still today in the face of truth as told from his perspective.\u003cbr /\u003eA point that Chris articulates well is that he fell in love with the “real” Selena. And that is the Selena he presents page by page, word by word. The examples he shares are intimate and simplistic, yet bring an extraordinarily powerful presence to Selena’s memory. This is not an easy task and Chris must be commended for letting his authentic spirit vividly recall the eternal love of his life.\u003cbr /\u003eI connected with many of the childhood memories Chris shared partly because we are from the same city and age range, but mostly because our economic backgrounds were similar. I found myself laughing when he mentioned his mom loving 55KTSA because my mom did as well. So much so, that I have pictures of me as a child covered in 55KTSA buttons and clothing she made for a radio sponsored contest!\u003cbr /\u003eI felt deep sadness in moments when Chris discusses being deemed unworthy of Selena’s affections. To me, this must have worn heavily on his core sense of self. Chris, however, ultimately transcends those feelings and comes to a place of assured certainty in both his love for Selena and of her love for him!\u003cbr /\u003eSo many moments are retold with such precision that brief flashes of the Selena movie played in my brain. I especially enjoyed seeing Selena’s playful nature highlighted as one of her best attributes.\u003cbr /\u003eChris will make you cry when retelling the painful moments of Selena’s death and his reactions that followed. The tear-jerker moment for me (and there were many) is his attempt at preserving her scent after her death. I won’t reveal the details but warn you that you better have a box of tissue nearby.\u003cbr /\u003eUltimately, this book is about the resurrection of Chris Perez and his “struggle to find meaning in life again”. It is about freeing himself from the walls of his grief and deciding to return to the land of the living. This book is his “best I can” moment.\u003cbr /\u003e“I love you, Christopher,” Selena said. She always used my full name whenever things were serious or intense between us. ��Let’s never let anything between us change. Promise?” Her voice was as solemn as I’d ever heard it. “I promise,” I said, and told her how much I loved her, too. “I don’t know what I’d do if I ever lost you,” I confessed. \u003cbr /\u003eChris Perez wrote a book, for Selena, and that’s how the story really ends.\u003cbr /\u003e","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/9347538?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/325648296"},"likeCount":17,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":1,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:12859648":{"id":12859648,"__typename":"User","legacyId":12859648,"imageUrlSquare":"","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":4,"viewableName":"Gabriella Sanders","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/12859648-gabriella-sanders","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":0},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.GFap4u2BGwjGsxo4dnDcQw":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.GFap4u2BGwjGsxo4dnDcQw","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.OBfo01am2p3jpPbtKc27LQ"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:12859648"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1612934738053,"createdAt":1351537749000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1351542666000,"text":"Chris Perez's purpose in writing \"To Selena, With Love\" was to give everyone a piece of their life. Chris Perez wanted to give his personal perspective on Selena. Another purpose could be that, he wanted to present a side of Selena to her fans so that they knew that she was just like everyone else. In an interview he did with CNN news, he said he was comfortable putting her life into a book. He said himself that he wanted to share her life, their life, together. Perez's purpose was to unwind and let go of suppressed feelings he's had for years.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eTo Selena, With love isn't a novel where you can relate. It is a good book, but it's nothing that'll leave a lasting impact. Sure, the book will leave you in a state of \"awe\", but that's because the book is filled with different types of emotions. This novel offers an arrange of emotions ranging from historical laughter, to having you on the edge of your seat ready to cry. \"Abraham looked at me with dull eyes and said, 'Selena passed away, Chris. She's dead. She was shot and she's dead.\" (p. 266) Perez previously states how he basically hated himself for awhile for even letting Selena go to a motel with someone he had never really trusted in the first place.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThe greatest strengths of the book was how the author could draw almost any reaction out of you. Chris Perez surely does have a way with words. He described Selena right down to the \"T\". As for weaknesses, I found nothing wrong with the novel. Maybe a few spelling errors here and there, but otherwise it was a fantastic novel to read. Once you pick up this book you will never want to put it down. Once the book ends, you will be filled with enraged sadness because you don't want it to end. Perez took this novel to a whole other level. He went into full-on detail about every aspect in their life from the first day he met her. \"When we lose people who who are precious to us, we all have to grieve in our own ways.\" (p. 4)\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThis novel is good for anybody who can relate to losing a loved one. I can say I related to both Chris and Selena in this novel. Chris was forbidden from seeing/keeping in contact with Selena but he defied authority (Selena's father) and he was given the cold shoulder. I've never been in that particular situation but I have been restricted from getting/doing something. \"I don't know what's going on with you guys, but whatever it is, it stops right now.\" (p. 73) I related to Selena because, Selena was the baby of the family and everyone was super protective over her. I am not the baby of the family but I am the only girl, which means I am watched like a hawk...by everyone. At first I can honestly say I found the book just a tad bit boring, but about 2-3 pages in I was instantly in love with it \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e \u003cbr /\u003eI was too young to even know or care about Selena Quintanilla, but when I saw her movie (acted out by Jennifer Lopez) I instantly became infatuated with her. I had to have watched that movie a good 5 times and listen to all of her music ever created.In my personal opinion, this book has taught me the lesson of \"Don't judge a book by it's cover\". Before even reading the book or seeing the movie, an aundance of people would talk about her and I would say \"who is that?\" When I found out, Selena's husband had written a book about her I HAD to have it. This book brought out every emotion you could ever possibly think of. This is a wonderful book. I have reread this novel over 10 times, I just love the book that much I would most definitely recommend this book to someone. I would even recommend it to someone who has never even heard of Selena Quintanilla-Perez. ","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/12859648?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/444214225"},"likeCount":14,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.T9vDYCX7ayDwzVs2m-uebg":{"id":"kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.T9vDYCX7ayDwzVs2m-uebg","__typename":"Contributor","works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":16}},"User:5827355":{"id":5827355,"__typename":"User","legacyId":5827355,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1442617261i/5827355._UX200_CR0,33,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":true,"textReviewsCount":114,"viewableName":"Jamie White","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/5827355-jamie-white","contributor":{"__ref":"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.T9vDYCX7ayDwzVs2m-uebg"},"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":64},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.KGqmWZ_Nl87xn7FuknQxNQ":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.KGqmWZ_Nl87xn7FuknQxNQ","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.OBfo01am2p3jpPbtKc27LQ"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:5827355"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1641272858841,"createdAt":1338476332000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1339002184000,"text":"I was just beginning to learn Spanish in school when Selena was murdered back in 1995. I remembered hearing a story or two about \"The Mexican Madonna\" before her passing, but never heard her music. At the time, I didn't know Spanish and just wasn't interested. Then \"I Could Fall in Love\" and \"Dreaming Of You\" came out. Without knowing who it was, I instantly connected with the music and the voice coming over my radio. I was sad to discover that the same person singing was the one who I'd read about not long before as the details of her murder became national news. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThose two songs introduced me to Selena, the artist, and Spanish music. Since becoming a fan, I've seen the movie and read another bio about her, so much of what was contained in here was no surprise. What was interesting about it, though, was the outsider's perspective. Chris Perez was an outsider in the Quintanilla family in many respects. He was not accepted by Abraham as a suitable boyfriend/husband for Selena until Selena and Chris decided to elope and force the issue of their relationship. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThere were a couple of surprises. I had no idea, for example, that the rest of the Quintanilla family and the Dinos basically turned their backs on Chris at one point. They wanted to avoid dealing with Abraham's temper as the relationship came to light despite the fact they'd been supportive beforehand. I was also surprised by the fact Selena herself had revealed Yolanda showed her a gun prior to that fateful meeting March 31st. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eOverall, Chris Perez has written a moving and engaging account of his life with The Queen of Tejano music and the aftermath of her murder. You feel his emotions and I couldn't help but smile as he shares a few details of his life now, having pulled himself out of a grief that looked as thought it may destroy him. ","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/5827355?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/339964914"},"likeCount":13,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:4340064":{"id":4340064,"__typename":"User","legacyId":4340064,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1285522561i/4340064.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":77,"viewableName":"Devika Koppikar","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/4340064-devika-koppikar","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":8},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.vY_Uq-wGUw4KAecibKArZA":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.vY_Uq-wGUw4KAecibKArZA","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.OBfo01am2p3jpPbtKc27LQ"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:4340064"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1642620209137,"createdAt":1372616803000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1372616938000,"text":"\tI read this book because I’ve been a Selena fan for almost 20 years and wanted to learn more about the person behind the image. Before I detail my thoughts on this book, let me first describe what Selena means to me.\u003cbr /\u003e\tSelena entered my life on the day that she died. Because I was home sick that day, I caught a glimpse of the tragic news on the television programs I normally did not watch. Then, in the days that followed, I saw tributes to Selena which were ubiquuous in Texas, where I lived at the time. People expressed their sorrow with signage and banners on their cars, homes, trees and poles. Mainstream radio stations played her music and her voice captured me. A few months later, I read an article about how Chris Perez was coping with his loss. That’s when I became totally enmeshed with her. She was the same age as me and like me, had brown skin and black hair. Yet, she didn’t let racism thwart her ambition. She had accomplished so much, influenced so many, and had a plethora of plans for the future. I, on the other hand, was in a dark place in my own life. At the time, I hated my job, was confused about my goals, avoided my community, and worst of all, attracted a dreary set of peers. \u003cbr /\u003e\tBut I believe in death, from the other world, Selena resurrected me. Through listening to all her songs and reading about her, I purged all the negative energy from my spirit. I rewrote my job description, surrounded myself with energetic and positive people and not only got involved with the community, but climbed my way into a leadership position. It’s 18 years later, and my find myself in another valley, but after reading this book, I realized that Selena never turned 40, never had children and never got to actualize her dreams in life. But I still can. \u003cbr /\u003e\tNow, about this book. I gave it an average rating because while it filled in a lot of gaps about Selena’s life, it didn’t grip me as I hoped it would. Maybe I’ve grown older and wiser and find it difficult to relate to Selena’s non-stop energy, impulsive behavior, and what I perceive as self-centeredness. For example, when Chris said he contemplated leaving Los Dinos to pursue his own interest in rock music, she threatened to leave him. While Chris wrote that he got over this, I thought it was manipulative, domineering and selfish on her part. Maybe he agreed to it at the time and today justifies it due to her tragic death, but had she still been alive, how long would anyone be able to put up with something like this? Second, when he discussed her buying dog after dog after dog, I thought it was immature and indulgent. If she wanted something, she got it; if she wanted to do something (like ride motorcycle), she did it—without thinking it through. Perhaps that works for a 20-something music star, but at some point, life teaches you that you can’t splurge on whatever you want, whenever you want and that not everything you do has a positive outcome. Unfortunately, Selena was robbed from living and could not gain this wisdom. \u003cbr /\u003e\tHaving said this, I think there was more to Selena than what Chris has shared in this book. I think she did have extensive wisdom, maturity and depth than what was described in these pages. I understand that Chris is a private person and is not obligated to share his deepest thoughts and feelings about Selena. Still, his antedotes and stories only touched the surface. I just shared how Selena changed me. I wish Chris had provided a more in-depth account of how Selena changed him. Sure, he does state that she changed him into a more loving person. But what I would have wanted to know more in-depth is:\u003cbr /\u003e•\tHow he was before he met Selena. For example, he mentions having girlfriends, but not experiencing anything deep. Well, what was that like? Why was he that way? How did his parents’ divorce and upbringing influence him?\u003cbr /\u003e•\tWhat was it about Selena that changed him? Her forgiveness and understanding isn’t sufficient. Because of his parents’ divorce and humble beginnings, he had to have had trust issues. How did Selena change that. \u003cbr /\u003e•\tHow he dealt with the tragedy in terms of his emotions and actions. He mentions heavy drinking, drugs, depression and going crazy. But what were his days like? How was Selena’s family, who lived right next door, toward him? Did he contemplate killing himself? Did he go back to his old ways? Did he lose his zest for life?\u003cbr /\u003e•\tHow then did he come out of these dark days? How did Selena (in death) influence him? Again, he does mention the band he started, getting remarried and having kids. But I would have liked to hear more. How does his life with Selena influence him in the way he raises his children? Does he mention Selena to them? What about the mother of his children? I think her name is Vanessa and they’re now divorced. Did his life with Selena shadow and eventually end their marriage? Finally, how does he think Selena would have been today, had she not been killed?\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI am glad I read the book and by no means has it made me think less of Chris or Selena. I’m just saying I would like to have had more. It would have only strengthen Selena’s legacy.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e","rating":3,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/4340064?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/655159701"},"likeCount":12,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":2,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Work:kca://work/amzn1.gr.work.v1.FXiIhUr8-2HzTPI_v8tsqA":{"id":"kca://work/amzn1.gr.work.v1.FXiIhUr8-2HzTPI_v8tsqA","__typename":"Work","legacyId":19120179,"bestBook":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.OBfo01am2p3jpPbtKc27LQ"},"details":{"__typename":"WorkDetails","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/work/19120179-to-selena-with-love","shelvesUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/work/shelves/19120179-to-selena-with-love","publicationTime":1331020800000,"originalTitle":"","awardsWon":[],"places":[],"characters":[{"__typename":"Character","name":"Selena Quintanilla","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/characters/1024218-selena-quintanilla"},{"__typename":"Character","name":"Chris Perez","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/characters/1046964-chris-perez"}]},"reviews":{"__typename":"BookReviewsConnection","totalCount":718,"edges":[{"__typename":"BookReviewsEdge","node":{"__ref":"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.0y3aBEenKqZcfYcJw3hcdA"}},{"__typename":"BookReview